   <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomical_object"
 ] .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000810
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000810> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000267> ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "An atmosphere which surrounds a planet." ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo#envoPolar> ;
                                               rdfs:label "planetary atmosphere"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000813
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000813> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040>
                                                                                          [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                            owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> ;
                                                                                            owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000799>
                                                                                          ]
                                                                                        ) ;
                                                                     rdf:type owl:Class
                                                                   ] ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000040> ,
                                                               [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                 owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> ;
                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000799>
                                                               ] ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A material part of an astronomical body." ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> "Also note that some astronomical body parts (ABPs) may have fiat boundaries: if there's strong debate about where an ABP begins or ends (over and above fuzzy boundaries), with different official classifications setting different thresholds or limits, axiomatise the class with fiat boundaries of the appropriate dimension."@en ,
                                                                                            "Note that material entities may have immaterial entities (e.g. sites) as parts."@en ,
                                                                                            "This class includes material parts of astronomical bodies. Immaterial parts, such as magnetospheres, are represented as sites under the influence of magnetic fields.Please post countercases in the ENVO tracker for revision of this hierarchy if needed."@en ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo#envoAstro> ,
                                                                                                       <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo#envoPolar> ;
                                               rdfs:comment "Material parts of astronomical bodies generally have boundaries formed by discontinuities in qualities, composition, or other physical characterisitcs. These boundaries are sometimes sharp, and sometimes diffuse, with different classification systems and communities declaring varying thresholds (e.g. for where a shoreline, forest, or other entity begins and ends). However, some boundaries are declared by fiat - that is, by arbitrary human convention or decree - particularly by regulatory or other authorities and communities of practice. The classes in this hierarchy attempt to offer generalisable definitions that allow multiple classfiication systems to map to and interoperate through. If desired, we can create classes that declare thresholds used by a given authority or community under the more generic ones, annotated with source information."@en ;
                                               rdfs:label "astronomical body part"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000814
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000814> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_00010483>
                                                                                          [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                            owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> ;
                                                                                            owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001546>
                                                                                          ]
                                                                                        ) ;
                                                                     rdf:type owl:Class
                                                                   ] ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_00010483> ,
                                                               [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                 owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> ;
                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001546>
                                                               ] ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "An environmental material which is in a solid state." ;
                                               rdfs:comment "This is a defined class: its subclasses will not be asserted, but filled by inference." ;
                                               rdfs:label "solid environmental material"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000815
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000815> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_00010483>
                                                                                          [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                            owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> ;
                                                                                            owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001548>
                                                                                          ]
                                                                                        ) ;
                                                                     rdf:type owl:Class
                                                                   ] ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02000140> ,
                                                               [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                 owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> ;
                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001548>
                                                               ] ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "An environmental material which is in a liquid state." ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo#envoPolar> ;
                                               rdfs:comment "This is a defined class: most of its subclasses will not be asserted, but filled by inference." ;
                                               rdfs:label "liquid environmental material"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000817
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000817> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000813> ,
                                                               [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                 owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> ;
                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PCO_0000000>
                                                               ] ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "An astronomical body part which includes all the living entities within the gravitational sphere of influence of that body, as well as the non-living and dead entities with which they interact."@en ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> "Whether this class should be grouped with classes such as \"hydrosphere\" and \"cryosphere\" requires some discussion." ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo#envoAstro> ,
                                                                                                       <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo#envoPolar> ;
                                               rdfs:comment "The gravitational sphere of influence referenced in this class' definition is the Hill sphere: a region in which an object dominates the attraction of satellites despite gravitational perturbations." ;
                                               rdfs:label "biosphere"@en .

[ rdf:type owl:Axiom ;
   owl:annotatedSource <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000817> ;
   owl:annotatedProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> ;
   owl:annotatedTarget "An astronomical body part which includes all the living entities within the gravitational sphere of influence of that body, as well as the non-living and dead entities with which they interact."@en ;
   <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "http://www.biology-online.org/dictionary/Biosphere" ,
                                                            "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biosphere"
 ] .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000819
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000819> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01001477> ,
                                                               [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                 owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002473> ;
                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_00002006>
                                                               ] ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "An astronomical body part which is composed of the combined mass of water found on, under, and over the surface of a planet." ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo#envoAstro> ,
                                                                                                       <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo#envoPolar> ;
                                               rdfs:comment "This is a very broad and, in practice, poorly defined term. Please consider using or requesting a more specific class." ;
                                               rdfs:label "hydrosphere"@en .

[ rdf:type owl:Axiom ;
   owl:annotatedSource <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000819> ;
   owl:annotatedProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> ;
   owl:annotatedTarget "An astronomical body part which is composed of the combined mass of water found on, under, and over the surface of a planet." ;
   <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hydrosphere"
 ] .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000875
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000875> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03000010> ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A precipitation process is a process in which a portion of some substance segregates from a material in which that substance or its precursors were dissolved or suspended in and settles due to a force such as gravity or centrifugal force." ;
                                               rdfs:label "precipitation process"@en .

[ rdf:type owl:Axiom ;
   owl:annotatedSource <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000875> ;
   owl:annotatedProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> ;
   owl:annotatedTarget "A precipitation process is a process in which a portion of some substance segregates from a material in which that substance or its precursors were dissolved or suspended in and settles due to a force such as gravity or centrifugal force." ;
   <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Precipitation_%28chemistry%29" ;
   rdfs:comment "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Precipitation"
 ] .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000944
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000944> rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                               rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000776> ;
                                               <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A piece of plastic which has a diameter less than five millimetres." ;
                                               <http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor> <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2996-719X> ,
                                                                                             <https://orcid.org/0000-0002-8166-0486> ,
                                                                                             <https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1072-8081> ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasRelatedSynonym> "microplastic" ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#inSubset> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/envo#envoPlastics> ;
                                               rdfs:comment "This classification is based on the thresholds detailed in GESAMP report # 99 on recommendation from the SDG 14 indicator team. While the definition is in accordance with the common use of this term (as per GESAMP report # 99), alternative size classifications exist. Alternative classifications are a piece of plastic which is between 1 and 5 millimetres in diameter, a piece of plastic which has a diameter less than 1 millimetre, or a piece of plastic which has a diameter greater than 330 micrometres. The use of the word diameter in this case was understood to mean the generalised form of diameter, i.e. the largest distance between two points belonging to an object."@en ;
                                               rdfs:label "microplastic particle"@en .

[ rdf:type owl:Axiom ;
   owl:annotatedSource <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000944> ;
   owl:annotatedProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> ;
   owl:annotatedTarget "A piece of plastic which has a diameter less than five millimetres." ;
   <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microplastics" ,
                                                            "https://marinedebris.noaa.gov/file/2192/download?token=5dvqb-YY"
 ] .

[ rdf:type owl:Axiom ;
   owl:annotatedSource <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000944> ;
   owl:annotatedProperty rdfs:comment ;
   owl:annotatedTarget "This classification is based on the thresholds detailed in GESAMP report # 99 on recommendation from the SDG 14 indicator team. While the definition is in accordance with the common use of this term (as per GESAMP report # 99), alternative size classifications exist. Alternative classifications are a piece of plastic which is between 1 and 5 millimetres in diameter, a piece of plastic which has a diameter less than 1 millimetre, or a piece of plastic which has a diameter greater than 330 micrometres. The use of the word diameter in this case was understood to mean the generalised form of diameter, i.e. the largest distance between two points belonging to an object."@en ;
   <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> <http://www.gesamp.org/publications/guidelines-for-the-monitoring-and-assessment-of-plastic-litter-in-the-ocean>
 ] .


